Reusing Existing Service Layer POJOs in REST Modernization
1. Objective

The purpose of this document is to outline the approach for reusing existing service-layer POJOs and business logic directly in the new REST-based architecture, after removing the legacy SOAP façade.
This approach ensures maximum reuse, minimizes regression, and reduces modernization complexity.

2. Background
Aspect	Current (Legacy)	Target (Modernized)
API Interface	SOAP over HTTP (Apache CXF)	REST over HTTPS (JSON)
Presentation Layer	SOAP service classes (CXF-generated)	Spring Boot REST controllers
Business Layer	Custom service classes (Spring beans)	Reused as-is
Data Layer	DAO / Repository layer	Reused as-is
Serialization	XML (JAXB)	JSON (Jackson)

The current SOAP service layer consists of CXF-generated endpoints that receive JAXB-bound request/response objects and pass them to the service layer. The modernization replaces this SOAP binding layer with Spring Boot REST controllers, but retains the service and DAO layers unchanged.

